# Software Creation Proposal

## Project Title
Process Models Management System

## Objective
To develop a software application that helps users manage, visualize, and analyze various software process models efficiently.

## Scope
- Support for multiple process models (e.g., Waterfall, Agile, Spiral)
- Visualization tools for process flows
- User-friendly interface for creating and editing models
- Export and import functionality for model data
- Reporting and analytics features

## Target Users
- Software engineering students
- Project managers
- Software development teams

## Technology Stack
- Frontend: React.js
- Backend: Node.js with Express
- Database: MongoDB
- Visualization: D3.js

## Timeline
- Requirements Gathering: 1 week
- Design & Prototyping: 2 weeks
- Development: 4 weeks
- Testing: 2 weeks
- Deployment: 1 week

## Expected Outcomes
- A functional web application for managing software process models
- Documentation and user manual
- Source code repository

## Team Roles
- Project Manager
- Frontend Developer
- Backend Developer
- QA Engineer

## Budget Estimate
- Development: $X,XXX
- Testing: $X,XXX
- Deployment: $X,XXX

## Conclusion
This proposal outlines the plan to create a Process Models Management System to aid in software engineering education and practice.